<div class="page-head"><h2>Tutorial · 3D Shooter</h2></div>

<DocsPage Slug="tutorial-3d-shooter">
    <h1>Build a 3D multiplayer arena shooter</h1>
    <p class="lead">
        A third-person arena where players drive around and shoot each other with hitscan weapons.
        Same toolkit as the 2D tutorial — matchmaking, the <a href="/dashboard/docs/sync-nodes">SpawnSync</a>
        node for movement, the event relay for shots, and per-player health — applied in 3D, with the
        whole scene built in code.
    </p>

    <p style="margin:10px 0">
        <span class="badge badge-cyan">Matchmaking</span>
        <span class="badge badge-cyan">SpawnSync</span>
        <span class="badge badge-cyan">Realtime events</span>
        <span class="badge badge-green">Hitscan · damage · respawn</span>
    </p>

    <div class="banner banner-warn">
        <span>📋</span>
        <span>New here? Start with the <a href="/dashboard/docs/getting-started">Quickstart</a> and save
            your public key in the <strong>SpawnWeaver dock</strong>. The
            <a href="/dashboard/docs/tutorial-2d-shooter">2D shooter</a> explains the model in a bit more
            detail — this page mirrors it in 3D.</span>
    </div>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>SpawnSync owns movement.</strong> Each player is a small scene (a capsule) with a
            <strong>SpawnSync</strong> child. On the copy you control it streams your position, rotation,
            and <code>hp</code>; on other players it interpolates the capsule toward their updates. No
            <code>patch_entity_state</code>, no interpolation code.</li>
        <li><strong>Hitscan shots are events.</strong> Firing sends a <code>shoot</code> event with a ray
            (origin + direction). Everyone draws a tracer; each client tests the ray against <em>its own</em>
            player and, if hit, lowers its own <code>hp</code> (which replicates via SpawnSync). No bullets
            to simulate.</li>
        <li><strong>Tank controls</strong> (Left/Right turn, Up/Down drive, Space shoot) — keyboard only,
            no mouse capture.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>1. The player scene</h2>
    <p>Make a <strong>Node3D</strong> scene saved as <code>player.tscn</code> and attach this script — it
        just builds the capsule + a barrel that shows facing. SpawnSync does the networking.</p>
    <pre>extends Node3D
## A 3D player avatar. The SpawnSync child streams position, rotation, and hp.

var color := Color.WHITE
var hp: int = 100

func _ready() -> void:
    var mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()
    mat.albedo_color = color

    var body := MeshInstance3D.new()
    var capsule := CapsuleMesh.new()
    capsule.radius = 0.5
    capsule.height = 2.0
    body.mesh = capsule
    body.position = Vector3(0, 1.0, 0)        # stand it on the ground
    body.material_override = mat
    add_child(body)

    var barrel := MeshInstance3D.new()        # points +Z so you can see which way it faces
    var box := BoxMesh.new()
    box.size = Vector3(0.2, 0.2, 1.2)
    barrel.mesh = box
    barrel.position = Vector3(0, 1.0, 0.8)
    barrel.material_override = mat
    add_child(barrel)</pre>
    <p>Then add the networking with one node: select the root, <em>Add Child Node</em> →
        <strong>SpawnSync</strong>, and in its Inspector set <em>Sync position</em> + <em>Sync rotation</em>
        on, <em>Synced properties</em> = <code>hp</code>, and <em>Send rate</em> = <code>12</code> (headroom
        under the rate limit so shoot events get through). Save the scene.</p>

    <h2>2. The arena scene</h2>
    <p>Make a <strong>Node3D</strong> scene saved as <code>arena_3d.tscn</code>, set it as the main scene,
        attach a new script, and paste each part in order.</p>

    <h3>2a. Constants &amp; state</h3>
    <pre>extends Node3D
## 3D arena shooter (hitscan, free-for-all). Movement/hp via SpawnSync; shots via the event relay.

const GAME_MODE := "arena3d_ffa"
const MOVE_SPEED := 7.0
const TURN_SPEED := 2.6
const FIRE_COOLDOWN := 0.30
const MAX_HP := 100
const HIT_DAMAGE := 34
const HIT_RADIUS := 1.2
const ARENA_HALF := 28.0
const PlayerScene := preload("res://player.tscn")

var _status: Label
var _hud: Label
var _find_btn: Button
var _camera: Camera3D

var _in_match := false
var _respawning := false
var _fire_cd := 0.0
var _me: Node3D = null
var _remotes: Dictionary = {}     # entity_id -> player Node3D</pre>

    <h3>2b. Build the world</h3>
    <pre>func _build_world() -> void:
    var light := DirectionalLight3D.new()
    light.rotation_degrees = Vector3(-55, -40, 0)
    add_child(light)

    var world_env := WorldEnvironment.new()
    var env := Environment.new()
    env.background_mode = Environment.BG_COLOR
    env.background_color = Color(0.05, 0.04, 0.03)
    env.ambient_light_color = Color(0.40, 0.36, 0.30)
    env.ambient_light_energy = 0.6
    world_env.environment = env
    add_child(world_env)

    var ground := MeshInstance3D.new()
    var plane := PlaneMesh.new()
    plane.size = Vector2(ARENA_HALF * 2.0, ARENA_HALF * 2.0)
    ground.mesh = plane
    var gmat := StandardMaterial3D.new()
    gmat.albedo_color = Color(0.16, 0.13, 0.10)
    ground.material_override = gmat
    add_child(ground)

    _camera = Camera3D.new()
    _camera.position = Vector3(0, 10, 12)
    _camera.look_at(Vector3.ZERO, Vector3.UP)
    add_child(_camera)</pre>

    <h3>2c. Connect &amp; subscribe</h3>
    <pre>func _ready() -> void:
    _build_world()
    _build_ui()
    MultiplayerService.welcomed.connect(func(_id): _set_status("Connected. Click Find Match."))
    MultiplayerService.connection_error.connect(func(r): _set_status("Connection error: " + r))
    MultiplayerService.matchmaking_queued.connect(func(_m, _r, _s): _set_status("Searching for players…"))
    MultiplayerService.match_found.connect(_on_match_found)
    MultiplayerService.matchmaking_timeout.connect(func(_m, _r): _on_match_over("No match found — try again."))
    MultiplayerService.state_snapshot_received.connect(_on_snapshot)
    MultiplayerService.entity_state_changed.connect(func(id, _p, full): _ensure_remote(id, full))
    MultiplayerService.player_left.connect(func(_r, pid): _remove_remote(pid))
    MultiplayerService.event_received.connect(_on_event)</pre>

    <h3>2d. Spawn your player + a capsule per remote</h3>
    <pre>func _on_match_found(_room_id: String, room_code: String, _list: Array) -> void:
    _in_match = true
    _respawning = false
    _spawn_local()
    _find_btn.disabled = true
    _update_hud()
    _set_status("Match %s! Left/Right turn · Up/Down move · Space shoots." % room_code)

func _spawn_local() -> void:
    if _me != null:
        return
    _me = PlayerScene.instantiate()
    _me.color = Color(0.96, 0.70, 0.36)
    _me.position = _random_spawn()
    _me.get_node("SpawnSync").local = true   # SpawnSync registers + streams my transform and hp
    add_child(_me)

func _ensure_remote(id: String, state: Dictionary) -> void:
    if id == MultiplayerService.player_id or _remotes.has(id):
        return
    var p := PlayerScene.instantiate()
    p.color = Color(0.91, 0.44, 0.29)
    if state.has("x") and state.has("z"):    # start where the entity already is
        p.position = Vector3(float(state["x"]), 0.0, float(state["z"]))
    if state.has("hp"):
        p.hp = int(state["hp"])
    p.get_node("SpawnSync").entity_id = id   # remote: interpolate this capsule; auto-free on leave
    add_child(p)
    _remotes[id] = p

func _remove_remote(id: String) -> void:
    var p = _remotes.get(id, null)
    if p != null and is_instance_valid(p):
        p.queue_free()
    _remotes.erase(id)

func _on_snapshot(snapshot: Dictionary) -> void:
    for e in snapshot.get("entities", []):
        _ensure_remote(str(e.get("entityId", "")), e.get("state", {}))</pre>

    <h3>2e. Drive your player — only when this window is focused</h3>
    <p>You drive only <code>_me</code>; SpawnSync streams it. The <strong>focus guard</strong> means only
        the window you've clicked controls its player — handy when you run two instances on one PC to test.</p>
    <pre>func _process(delta: float) -> void:
    if not _in_match or _me == null:
        return
    _fire_cd = maxf(0.0, _fire_cd - delta)
    if not _respawning and get_window().has_focus():
        _handle_input(delta)
    _update_camera()

func _handle_input(delta: float) -> void:
    if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_left"):
        _me.rotation.y += TURN_SPEED * delta
    if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_right"):
        _me.rotation.y -= TURN_SPEED * delta
    var fwd := Vector3(sin(_me.rotation.y), 0.0, cos(_me.rotation.y))
    if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_up"):
        _me.position += fwd * MOVE_SPEED * delta
    if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_down"):
        _me.position -= fwd * MOVE_SPEED * delta
    _me.position.x = clampf(_me.position.x, -ARENA_HALF, ARENA_HALF)
    _me.position.z = clampf(_me.position.z, -ARENA_HALF, ARENA_HALF)
    if Input.is_action_pressed("ui_accept"):
        _try_fire(fwd)

func _update_camera() -> void:
    if _me == null:
        return
    var fwd := Vector3(sin(_me.rotation.y), 0.0, cos(_me.rotation.y))
    _camera.position = _me.position + Vector3(0, 6.0, 0) - fwd * 9.0
    _camera.look_at(_me.position + Vector3(0, 1.0, 0), Vector3.UP)</pre>

    <h3>2f. Hitscan shooting &amp; damage</h3>
    <pre>func _try_fire(fwd: Vector3) -> void:
    if _fire_cd > 0.0:
        return
    _fire_cd = FIRE_COOLDOWN
    var origin := _me.position + Vector3(0, 1.0, 0)
    MultiplayerService.send_event("shoot", {
        "ox": origin.x, "oy": origin.y, "oz": origin.z,
        "dx": fwd.x, "dy": fwd.y, "dz": fwd.z,
    })
    _spawn_tracer(origin, origin + fwd * 60.0)

func _on_event(event: String, data: Dictionary, _from_id: String) -> void:
    if event != "shoot":
        return
    var origin := Vector3(float(data.get("ox", 0)), float(data.get("oy", 0)), float(data.get("oz", 0)))
    var dir := Vector3(float(data.get("dx", 0)), float(data.get("dy", 0)), float(data.get("dz", 0)))
    _spawn_tracer(origin, origin + dir * 60.0)
    if _respawning or _me == null:
        return
    var me := _me.position + Vector3(0, 1.0, 0)
    var t := (me - origin).dot(dir)        # distance along the ray to my chest
    if t &lt; 0.0:
        return                              # I'm behind the shooter
    if (origin + dir * t).distance_to(me) &lt;= HIT_RADIUS:
        _take_hit()

func _take_hit() -> void:
    _me.hp -= HIT_DAMAGE      # SpawnSync replicates the new hp
    _update_hud()
    if _me.hp &lt;= 0:
        _respawn()
    else:
        _set_status("Hit! HP %d" % _me.hp)

func _respawn() -> void:
    _respawning = true
    _set_status("Fragged! Respawning…")
    await get_tree().create_timer(1.5).timeout
    _me.position = _random_spawn()
    _me.hp = MAX_HP
    _respawning = false
    _update_hud()
    _set_status("Fight! Left/Right turn · Up/Down move · Space shoots.")</pre>

    <h3>2g. Tracer, HUD &amp; connect controls</h3>
    <pre>func _on_match_over(reason: String) -> void:
    _in_match = false
    _find_btn.disabled = false
    _set_status(reason)

func _spawn_tracer(a: Vector3, b: Vector3) -> void:
    var im := ImmediateMesh.new()
    im.surface_begin(Mesh.PRIMITIVE_LINES)
    im.surface_add_vertex(a)
    im.surface_add_vertex(b)
    im.surface_end()
    var mi := MeshInstance3D.new()
    mi.mesh = im
    var mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()
    mat.shading_mode = BaseMaterial3D.SHADING_MODE_UNSHADED
    mat.albedo_color = Color(1.0, 0.9, 0.6)
    mi.material_override = mat
    add_child(mi)
    get_tree().create_timer(0.05).timeout.connect(mi.queue_free)

func _random_spawn() -> Vector3:
    return Vector3(randf_range(-ARENA_HALF + 3.0, ARENA_HALF - 3.0), 0.0,
        randf_range(-ARENA_HALF + 3.0, ARENA_HALF - 3.0))

func _my_name() -> String:
    return "P%d" % (randi() % 1000)

func _build_ui() -> void:
    var layer := CanvasLayer.new()
    add_child(layer)
    var bar := HBoxContainer.new()
    bar.position = Vector2(16, 16)
    bar.add_theme_constant_override("separation", 8)
    layer.add_child(bar)
    var connect_btn := Button.new()
    connect_btn.text = "Connect"
    connect_btn.pressed.connect(_on_connect)
    bar.add_child(connect_btn)
    _find_btn = Button.new()
    _find_btn.text = "Find Match"
    _find_btn.disabled = true
    _find_btn.pressed.connect(_on_find)
    bar.add_child(_find_btn)
    _status = Label.new()
    _status.position = Vector2(16, 56)
    _status.text = "Click Connect (uses the key saved in the SpawnWeaver dock)."
    layer.add_child(_status)
    _hud = Label.new()
    _hud.position = Vector2(16, 84)
    layer.add_child(_hud)

func _update_hud() -> void:
    _hud.text = "HP %d" % _me.hp if _me != null else ""

func _on_connect() -> void:
    if MultiplayerService.connect_using_config():
        _set_status("Connecting…")
        _find_btn.disabled = false
    else:
        _set_status("Save your public key in the SpawnWeaver dock first.")

func _on_find() -> void:
    if not MultiplayerService.is_connected_to_server():
        _set_status("Connect first.")
        return
    MultiplayerService.join_matchmaking(GAME_MODE, "", 2, _my_name())
    _find_btn.disabled = true
    _set_status("Searching for players…")

func _set_status(text: String) -> void:
    _status.text = text</pre>

    <h2>3. Play it with two windows</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><em>Debug → Run Multiple Instances</em>, set <strong>2</strong>, and run the scene.</li>
        <li>In both windows: <strong>Connect</strong> → <strong>Find Match</strong> to be paired into the
            same arena.</li>
        <li><strong>Click a window to focus it</strong>, then Left/Right turn, Up/Down drive, Space shoots.
            Line up your barrel and fire; the HUD shows your HP. Watch sessions on the
            <a href="/dashboard/debugger">Debugger</a>.</li>
    </ol>
    <div class="banner" style="border-color:var(--border);color:var(--steel)">
        <span>🎮</span>
        <span>Two windows on one PC share one keyboard, so you drive whichever is focused (that's the focus
            guard). For two players at once, run it on <strong>two machines</strong> (or with two people).
            Latency is dominated by distance to your server's region — pick a region near your players.</span>
    </div>
    <p class="muted">More players? Raise the match size in
        <code>join_matchmaking(GAME_MODE, "", 2, …)</code> (e.g. <code>4</code>).</p>

    <h2>Extend it</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Mouse-look &amp; strafing</strong> — capture the mouse and aim with it; keep the focus
            guard so a background instance doesn't track your cursor.</li>
        <li><strong>Physics &amp; cover</strong> — give players a <code>CharacterBody3D</code> and add
            obstacle meshes; raycast the physics world for line-of-sight.</li>
        <li><strong>More synced state</strong> — add fields like <code>team</code> to SpawnSync's
            <em>Synced properties</em> and they replicate automatically.</li>
        <li><strong>Persist stats</strong> — store wins/kills with player storage (see
            <a href="/dashboard/docs/tutorial-profile">Save a player profile</a>).</li>
    </ul>

